timeline.bodyText:
I like to include the original exception message when rethrowing an error because in many contexts, the user will only see this message, and it can be confusing not to include the more detailed message. So I frequently do this:
throw new RuntimeException("Unable to deploy databases indexes after updating entity models; cause: " + e.getMessage(), e);

I also think it's better to say "Unable to deploy database indexes", which is more clear than "index configuration".

